02/09/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- German Foreign Minister Joschka Fischer said his country would continue to support Romania's efforts to join the EU in 2007.
Visiting Bucharest on Monday (1 September), he met with his Romanian counterpart, Mircea Geoana, as well as with President Ion Iliescu and Prime Minister Adrian Nastase.
Afterwards, he urged authorities to proceed with necessary reforms and maintain good neighbourly relations.
In other news Monday, the Romanian Senate passed amendments to the constitution by a vote of 103-1.
Members of the opposition Greater Romania Party walked out before the vote, protesting certain provisions.
(Rompres, Mediafax - 01/09/03)
